-content/uploads/2015/01/DSC2761-300x201.jpg\" alt=\"\"]\r\n[image link=\"\" linktarget=\"_self\" image=\"https://lqustg.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/DSC2715-300x201.jpg\" alt=\"\"]\r\n[image link=\"\" linktarget=\"_self\" image=\"https://lqustg.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/DSC2659-300x201.jpg\" alt=\"\"]\r\n[image link=\"\" linktarget=\"_self\" image=\"https://lqustg.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/DSC1855-300x201.jpg\" alt=\"\"]\r\n[image link=\"\" linktarget=\"_self\" image=\"https://lqustg.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/DSC1794-300x201.jpg\" alt=\"\"]\r\n[image link=\"\" linktarget=\"_self\" image=\"https://lqustg.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/DSC1782-300x201.jpg\" alt=\"\"]\r\n[image link=\"\" linktarget=\"_self\" image=\"https://lqustg.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/DSC1741-300x201.jpg\" alt=\"\"]\r\n[image link=\"\" linktarget=\"_self\" image=\"https://lqustg.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/DSC2172-300x201.jpg\" alt=\"\"]\r\n[image link=\"\" linktarget=\"_self\" image=\"https://lqustg.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/DSC2165-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"\"]\r\n[image link=\"\" linktarget=\"_self\" image=\"https://lqustg.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/DSC2096-300x213.jpg\" alt=\"\"]\r\n[/images]','Home','','publish','closed','closed','','home','','','2019-07-02 18:56:15','2019-07-02 18:56:15','',0,'https://lqustg.wpengine.com/?page_id=7',0,'page','',0),(9,6,'2014-12-17 18:57:20','2014-12-17 18:57:20','<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\" style=\"color: #333333;\">Luther Quintana started his eponymous firm in 1987 and since then has become the premier purveyor of fine furniture and curtains to the design trade. His “get it done” attitude and unpretentious approach has garnered approval from some of the most respected designers and tastemakers in New York. His attention to detail is unrivaled. More importantly, his fervor for finishing each project well and on-time are the cornerstones of his firm.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\" style=\"color: #333333;\"> Luther Quintana <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Upholstery</span> is a full service <strong>upholstery</strong> firm with locations in NYC, Brooklyn and Suffolk County. Full service meaning that we build furniture from the frame stage until the very last tack or stitch, we make our own frames, paint them, prepare and upholster. The advantage of our full service capabilities is that our customers can see<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>EVERY SINGLE STEP as their ideas turn into luxurious goods. Our drapery department and showroom are located in Chelsea and have an additional showroom in Deer Park, New York. Our staff of 30 well-trained professionals are ready to take projects of any size.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">   </span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\" style=\"color: #333333;\"> Our approach is simple, work hard and keep our customers happy. Luther Quintana <em>Upholstery</em> has that hard work ethic instilled by our founder and carried on by his daughter, son, and by the versatile employees, many of which have been part of the firm since its inception.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\" style=\"color: #333333;\"> Works by Luther Quintana <em>Upholstery</em> can be seen in all the major home decor publications and in books by some of the most recognizable names in design. Each piece of furniture and every curtain photographed and published is a true testament to the hard work and dedication Luther Quintana and his firm have for their craft.</span></p>','About Us','','publish','closed','closed','','about-us','','','2015-06-15 16:54:23','2015-06-15 16:54:23','',0,'https://lqustg.wpengine.com/?page_id=9',0,'page','',0),(11,6,'2014-12-17 18:57:35','2014-12-17 18:57:35','<p class=\"p1\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">[title size=\"1\" content_align=\"left\" style_type=\"single solid\" sep_color=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]Frame Making/Woodworking:[/title]</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\" style=\"color: #333333;\">Luther Quintana Upholstery is one of a handful of firms that DO NOT outsource their frames elsewhere. This advantage makes for quicker lead-times and opportunities for <img class=\"  wp-image-246 alignright\" src=\"https://lqustg.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/IMG_2425-2-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"299\" height=\"224\" />designers to see their frames \"(at their request.)\" Frames can be altered or approved before upholstering. Our frames and our ability to make them in-house adds to the ultimate customization experience. When clients receive furniture from us it is truly bespoke and one-of-a-kind. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\" style=\"color: #333333;\">Luther Quintana Upholstery makes frames using the double-doweled joinery system, Kiln-dried maple frames and strong corner blocks. Oak or Mahogany legs are available in any design as well. Each step of the frame-making process ensures that each item will possess an heirloom quality and can be enjoyed for generations.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">[title size=\"1\" content_align=\"left\" style_type=\"single solid\" sep_color=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]Finishing:[/title]</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\" style=\"color: #333333;\">Our state-of-the art finishing booth allows us to make finish samples for approval by clients or replicate any desired finish, removing any doubts from their minds as to whether their end product will have the finish they demand. We can strip any paint or stain and leave faded, tarnished furniture looking new. Additionally, we can make reproductions of any antique furniture finishes if desired. We have hundreds of samples in our showrooms to choose from. We ceruse oak and bleach mahogany by hand-scraping the wood. This process gives the wood a rustic, more traditional look.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">[title size=\"1\" content_align=\"left\" style_type=\"single solid\" sep_color=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]Upholstery:[/title]</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\" style=\"color: #333333;\">We use jute webbing and coiled springs that are carefully hand tied to ensure even distribution of weight. Our upholsterers are trained to use the old-world method of horse hair and burlap. Each hand-made piece is padded with cotton and wrapped in down to ensure the highest standard of comfort. Our furniture, draperies and soft goods are hand sewn enclosed. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span style=\"color: #333333;\">[title size=\"1\" content_align=\"left\" style_type=\"single solid\" sep_color=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]Reupholstery:[/title]</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\" style=\"color: #333333;\">Luther Quintana Upholstery is an excellent resource for re-upholstery. Our woodworking department allows us to not only recover clients’ furniture but also allows us to reinforce any deficient frame. The reinforcement of old, worn, tarnished frames leaves them stronger and makes for a better finished product. Old cushions can be re-stuffed with new foam cores or filled in with down. Clients never have to worry about the integrity of the frame, finish of the legs or the cushions because we take care of everything under one roof!</span></p>','The Process','','publish','closed','closed','','the-process','','','2019-07-02 18:57:21','2019-07-02 18:57:21','',0,'https://lqustg.wpengine.com/?page_id=11',0,'page','',0),(13,6,'2014-12-17 18:58:01','2014-12-17 18:58:01','<p class=\"p1\">[title size=\"1\" content_align=\"left\" style_type=\"single solid\" sep_color=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]Window Treatments[/title]</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\" style=\"color: #333333;\">Decorators know all too well window treatments are an integral part of any well designed interior, and can add just the right finishing touch to form each room’s intended thought. A well selected window treatment should blend and balance each room’s interiors and not overpower it. Often the decision to do Roman shades or curtain panels can affect the overall character of the room since each determines the level of outdoor natural light and scenery. To coordinate a well-designed interior such drapery details as the number of pinch pleats, Hadley pleats, whether to add a soft or hard valance, operable or stationary panels, inset trims, contrast lining are just a few of the decisions each decorator will consider and determine. For some interiors sheer café curtains with hand-sewn rings are the perfect relaxed atmosphere. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\" style=\"color: #333333;\">What do decorators always look for when selecting an upholstery and <em>drapery</em> workroom? The answer is attention to detail and quality. There’s a world of difference when you compare a Roman shade sewn by hand with a contrast whip stitch as opposed to a Roman shade stitched with a sewing machine. Using a sewing machine is quicker, reduces labor cost, substitute’s quality and the finishing details look commercial. All <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">drapery</span> in our workroom is sewn by hand, the drapery rings are sewn by hand, all trims and details are hand stitched. We make sure to accomplish the decorator’s expectations and trust by maintaining a standard of excellence.</span></p>','Draperies','','publish','closed','closed','','draperies','','','2015-06-15 17:03:28','2015-06-15 17:03:28','',0,'https://lqustg.wpengine.com/?page_id=13',0,'page','',0),(15,6,'2014-12-17 18:58:20','2014-12-17 18:58:20','[title size=\"1\" content_align=\"left\" style_type=\"single solid\" sep_color=\"\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]Brooklyn Location[/title]\r\n[one_half last=\"no\" class=\"\" id=\"\"]<iframe style=\"border: 0;\" src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m14!1m8!1m3!1d3025.248474426729!2d-73.86989099999998!3d40.69052499999998!3m2!1i10